7712   // Note that stripPointerCastsSameRepresentation can strip off getelementptr
7713   // inbounds with zero offset. To guarantee that the result isn't poison, the
7714   // stripped pointer is checked as it has to be pointing into an allocated
7715   // object or be null `null` to ensure `inbounds` getelement pointers with a
7716   // zero offset could not produce poison.
7717   // It can strip off addrspacecast that do not change bit representation as
7718   // well. We believe that such addrspacecast is equivalent to no-op.
7719   auto *StrippedV = V->stripPointerCastsSameRepresentation();
